author: AudioBench
overview: Shapes the response of a value by limiting its rate of change, defined in dB per second.
details: The Ballistics module constrains how quickly a control value can rise or fall over time. It uses first-order smoothing based on a user-defined slope in dB per second, making it perfect for emulating analog meter ballistics or creating perceptually consistent smoothing for gain displays. Separate rise and fall parameters allow asymmetric dynamics matching VU, PPM, or custom metering standards.
